  "narrative": "Retnza's behavioral intelligence layer identifies 3 distinct subscriber groups discovered from usage, engagement, and lifecycle patterns across 9 behavioral dimensions. The solution applies kmeans clustering \u2014 selected after comparing three algorithms (K-Means, GMM, Agglomerative) across k=3\u20138 candidates. The optimal configuration (k=3) was chosen by maximising silhouette score (primary) with Davies-Bouldin index as tie-breaker, then validated for cluster stability across 5 random seeds (mean ARI: 0.999). Segments are well-separated on churn risk: the highest-risk group ('Early-Life At-Risk Users') shows 38.5% mean predicted risk \u2014 3.8\u00d7 the lowest-risk group \u2014 indicating meaningful behavioral differentiation. These are descriptive behavioral profiles discovered from subscriber data, not causal groupings. They are designed to guide retention prioritisation by surfacing which behavioral patterns are associated with above- or below-average churn risk."
